      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>This  short text is a list of ṣǝnǝʿt and ṣǝnṣǝnt days of the twelve months (sometimes thirteen, including Ṗagʷǝmen). The text is attested in a large number of manuscripts, most often as an addition. 
               The wording, as well as the number of ṣǝnǝʿt and ṣǝnṣǝnt days in each month, varies considerably across the witnesses. According to <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Grebaut1913Joursfastes"></ptr>
               </bibl>, the text is a list of lucky and unlucky days. Following the suggestions by Gasparini in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Gasparini1946Vocabili"/></bibl>, 
               Elagina, in <bibl> <ptr target="bm:Elagina2025Hassab"/></bibl>, argues that the text goes back to the long-standing tradition of moonwood, that is, the determination of days for cutting wood based on lunar phases. 
              </p>
         </abstract>
